o_bijou_governments_don_t_understand_cyber_warfare_we_need_hackers","viewed_count":1316447,"talks":[{"recommendations":{"status":"approved","headline":"Rodrigo Bijou recommends ","blurb":"Check out these resources on cyber warefare, curated by Rodrigo Bijou.","start_at":null,"end_at":null,"published":true,"eyebrow":null,"type":"recommendation","rec_lists":[{"title":"Reading list","description":"","rec_items":[{"label":"READ_Book","headline":"*Countdown to Zero Day: Stuxnet and the Launch of the World's First Digital Weapon*","blurb":"Kim Zetter’s account of Stuxnet, the digital weapon deployed by the US and Israel against Iran’s nuclear facilities in 2011, is an engaging read at the nexus of technology, global politics and the changing modern battlefield. The book is accessible for non-technical readers and provides a look into one of the first well-known, successful operations in cyber warfare. ","note":"Kim Zetter\r\nCrown, 2014","link_url":"http://www.amazon.com/Countdown-Zero-Day-Stuxnet-Digital/dp/077043617X/ref=as_li_tf_tl?ie=UTF8&camp=1789&creative=9325&creativeASIN=0520271440&linkCode=as2&tag=teco06-20","position":null,"is_pdf":false,"eyebrow":null},{"label":"READ_Article","headline":"\"The Untold Story of the Silk Road, Part 1\"","blurb":"Forget the so-called \"unicorn\" startups of Silicon Valley—in just a few years, twenty-something Ross Ulbricht built the Silk Road, a digital black market worth $1.2B in global transactions. This article chronicles the rise and fall of the market and its creator, showing the impact an individual can have challenging global law enforcement through new technology.","note":"Joshua Bearman and Tomer Hanuka\r\n*Wired*, May 2015","link_url":"http://www.wired.com/2015/04/silk-road-1/","position":null,"is_pdf":false,"eyebrow":null},{"label":"EXPLORE","headline":"\"Tangled Web: Law Enforcement Struggles to Control Darknet\"","blurb":"This article is my updated look at the challenges facing governments in policing the darker parts 